Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Yagba West Local Government Area of Kogi State, retired Major David Samuel, has denied issuing any letter to Barr. Babatunde Irukera, a governorship aspirant of the party who hails from the area. At a press conference, yesterday in Lokoja, the Yagba West APC chairman said a letter trending on the social media allegedly written by him after receiving some funds never emanated from him. “In the said letter, Barr. Babatunde Ayokunle Irukera claimed to have been responsible for the payment of rent for the party secretariat in Odo-Ere and payment of staff salaries of the APC in the council among others,” the chairman said. Daily Trust recalled that the APC screening committee for the Kogi governorship contest had disqualified 12 of the aspirants including Irukera over alleged irregularities. According to Major Samuel, “to the best of my knowledge, as the APC chairman for Yagba West Local Government Area, I wish to state clearly that I have never received a penny from Barr. Irukera, either directly or by proxy, since my assumption of office.” Kogi guber screening: APC chairman denies issuing letter to Irukera APC governorship primaries: The gladiators and new revelations in Kogi politics Groups differ over Bello in Kogi Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin